body: Would be nice if the log is containing a path: - to have it entirely - to make it a link for easy copy/paste and open on the IDE - Bonus -> if not a file supported by IDE, open it on OS file explorer (finder on Mac) ? My use case is that I print the path to the iOS SQLite Database because it's always a nightmare to find it. Would be perfect if when I click on the path it will open the folder on the finder for me to copy/paste the database where I need for debugging. ``` 10:42:49.711 6 info DatabaseProvider Database is: /Users/jaumard/Library/Developer/CoreSimulator/Devices/B9C382ED-425A-48A3-9DDA-B1C15D7BA485/data/Containers/Data/Ap... ```

comment_data.body:
Thanks for this @jaumard!

To confirm:

1. it looks like you're logging via a `developer:log` call?, and
2. the message is getting truncated, leading to an incomplete file URI?
Yes I'm using `developer:log`, message is truncated and it's not a link so I can't click or copy/paste it
@pq on last plugin version you pushed few days ago it's not truncated anymore but it's still not a link
Ok, great.  I'm glad things aren't truncating.  I'll update this issue to reflect the request for hyperlink support in message cell rendering.  Thanks!
Closing as this is related to the experimental logging view.
